Read GDAL feature thing 'what'

vapour_read_feature_what.Rd

Read GDAL geometry as blob, text, or numeric extent.

vapour_read_feature_what(dsource, layer = 0L, sql = "", what = "geometry",
  textformat = "json")

Arguments

dsource

data source
layer

layer
sql

sql
what

what to read, "geometry", "text", "extent"
textformat

indicate text output format, available are "json" (default), "gml", "kml", "wkt"

Details

vapour_read_feature_what will read a feature in various ways, as binary WKB, various text formats, a numeric extent, and for each an option SQL string will be evaluated against the data source before reading. The extent is the native bounding box, the four numbers xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax.

Examples

file <- "list_locality_postcode_meander_valley.tab"
mvfile <- system.file(file.path("extdata/tab", file), package="vapour")
#tib <- tibble::tibble(wkb = vapour_read_geometry(mvfile)) %>%
#  bind_cols(read_gdal_table(mvfile))
pfile <- system.file("extdata/point.shp", package = "vapour")
vapour_read_geometry(pfile)
